      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Design your own degradative pathway. You know the rules (organic mechanisms), and you’ve seen the kinds of reactions that occur in the biological degradation of fats and carbohydrates into acetyl CoA. If you were Mother Nature, what series of steps would you use to degrade the amino acid serine into acetyl CoA?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdU1aIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--4aab23bdb1f9b0bf82edb0bd4f25374438835309/OChem_29_EC_010.jpg\" alt=\"Serine reacts in the presence of unknown reagents, represented as a question mark, to form acetyl Co A.\">",
